37 static int
38 ExtensionChecksum(const std::string& s)
39 {
40 int length = Size(s);
41 int sum = 0;
42 for (int i = length - 2; i >= 0; i -= 2) {
43 sum += (int)s[i] - (int) '0';
44 }
45 sum *= 3;
46 for (int i = length - 1; i >= 0; i -= 2) {
47 sum += (int)s[i] - (int) '0';
48 }
49 sum *= 3;
50 return sum % 10;
51 }
52
53 static std::string
54 ParseExtension5String(const std::string& raw)
55 {
56 std::string currency;
57 switch (raw.front()) {
58 case '0':
59 case '1':
60 currency = "\xa3";
61 break;
62 case '3': // AUS
63 case '4': // NZ
64 case '5': // US
65 case '6': // CA
66 currency = "$";
67 break;
68 case '9':
69 // Reference: http://www.jollytech.com
70 if (raw == "90000") {
71 // No suggested retail price
72 return std::string();
73 }
74 if (raw == "99991") {
75 // Complementary
76 return "0.00";
77 }
78 if (raw == "99990") {
79 return "Used";
80 }
81 // Otherwise... unknown currency?
82 currency = "";
83 break;
84 default:
85 currency = "";
86 break;
87 }
88 int rawAmount = std::stoi(raw.substr(1));
89 std::stringstream buf;
90 buf << currency << std::fixed << std::setprecision(2) << (float(rawAmount) / 100);
91 return buf.str();
92 }

97static std::string
98DecodeMiddle(BitArray::Range* next_, int N)
99{
100 assert(N == 2 || N == 5);
101 int lgPatternFound = 0;
102 auto next = *next_;
103 std::string resultString;
104
105 for (int x = 0; x < N; x++) {
106 int bestMatch = UPCEANReader::DecodeDigit(&next, UPCEANCommon::L_AND_G_PATTERNS, &resultString);
107 if (bestMatch == -1)
108 return {};
109
110 // Read off separator if not last
111 if (x != N - 1 && !UPCEANReader::ReadGuardPattern(&next, std::array<int, 2>{1, 1}))
112 return {};
113
114 if (bestMatch >= 10)
115 lgPatternFound |= 1 << (N - 1 - x);
116 }
117
118 if (N == 2) {
119 if (std::stoi(resultString) % 4 != lgPatternFound)
120 return {};
121 } else {
122 constexpr int CHECK_DIGIT_ENCODINGS[] = {0x18, 0x14, 0x12, 0x11, 0x0C, 0x06, 0x03, 0x0A, 0x09, 0x05};
123 if (UPCEANExtension5Support::ExtensionChecksum(resultString) != IndexOf(CHECK_DIGIT_ENCODINGS, lgPatternFound))
124 return {};
125 }
126
127 *next_ = next;
128 return resultString;
129}
130
131static const std::array<int, 3> EXTENSION_START_PATTERN = { 1,1,2 };
132
133Result
134UPCEANExtensionSupport::DecodeRow(int rowNumber, const BitArray& row, BitArray::Iterator begin)
135{
136 BitArray::Range next = {row.getNextSet(begin), row.end()};
137
138 int xStart = static_cast<int>(next.begin - row.begin());
139
140 if (!UPCEANReader::ReadGuardPattern(&next, EXTENSION_START_PATTERN))
141 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
142
143 auto resultString = DecodeMiddle(&next, 5);
144 if (resultString.empty())
145 resultString = DecodeMiddle(&next, 2);
146
147 if (resultString.empty())
148 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
149
150 int xStop = static_cast<int>(next.begin - row.begin() - 1);
151
152 Result result(resultString, rowNumber, xStart, xStop, BarcodeFormat::UPC_EAN_EXTENSION);
153
154 if (resultString.size() == 2) {
155 result.metadata().put(ResultMetadata::ISSUE_NUMBER, std::stoi(resultString));
156 } else {
157 std::string price = UPCEANExtension5Support::ParseExtension5String(resultString);
158 if (!price.empty())
159 result.metadata().put(ResultMetadata::SUGGESTED_PRICE, TextDecoder::FromLatin1(price));
160 }
161
162 return result;
163}
